folder: Halsey Street & Wilson Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Halsey Street, west side, between Wilson and Knickerbocker Aves.
A view of the Irving Square Park.

1920.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing the northern end of the Park.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, looking southward. This block bounded by Weirfield and Halsey Streets and Wilson and Knickerbocker Aves., on the west, east, south and north respectively, was owned in 1869 by J. H. Bond.

1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Halsey Street & Wilson Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) Halsey Street, west side, south of Wilson Ave., showing the Halsey Street Presbyterian Church, which was formerly known as the German Evangelist Church.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing a closer view of the church from the opposite direction.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
